title: Zao Meng Zhe
synopsis:
The story will revolve around the virtual and real life, work, and feelings of the male protagonist Xiao Sa, telling an inspirational story of game players. The film is actually somewhat suspenseful and very realistic at the same time. I am afraid that for some viewers, this film is very literary. Although it is interspersed with majestic virtual worlds and various entanglements in the virtual world from time to time, this film , The description of contemporary young people is fairly successful.
This film pays great attention to the portrayal of characters, delicate performances, and emphasizes the concept of virtual actors. The era is moving more and more towards virtualization. Whether it is the booming development of the game industry or the virtual era that is constantly emphasized in major movies, it is slow Slowly emerges the concept that virtual actors will replace real actors? This will be a new movie model that may emerge. "Avatar" is doing a great job. With the advancement of technology, the cost will become smaller and smaller. It is naturally impossible for us to compare with any big movie that is really going to the theater. Just sneaked out a small step in this direction.
Therefore, in this film, we focus on depicting people and depicting a vivid virtual actor. The story itself is not a shocking event that saves the world and fights the devil. It starts from our lives, from the most basic, and talks about our players. The story, this is the first time our crew has produced a film in the mode of a movie. The engineering files produced by this film are more than all 7 episodes of "Warriors of the Alliance". The film length has reached 30 minutes, and the screen is more than "Warriors". With a qualitative leap, the action design has completely opened the distance. The plot has been carefully designed. Maybe some viewers may not understand it, but it doesn’t matter. Since the film runs only 30 minutes, we can’t talk too much. Complete, but every shot, every line, every plot has been designed, and the audience may find the answer in the film, or find the answer in reality.
(translated from douban)

title: Mao Yu Taohuayuan

A blanket for a domestic cat, who often stays in a daze on the windowsill, has been living comfortably with his son in a high-rise apartment in the city. One day the blanket and the cloak had to embark on an adventurous journey to find the peach blossom field of the legendary cat. At the same time, the blanket must face an unwillingness to mention a past in the heart. Perhaps this is also an important reason why the blanket is afraid of the outside world and unwilling to leave home...
(translated from douban)

title: Shi Er Shengxiao De Gushi

In each episode of the story, there will be an evil monster. Every time a monster is eliminated, an animal will give its life. To commemorate them, the animal becomes the zodiac of the year. The zodiac signs are an important part of Chinese traditional culture. This animation is telling the hero myth story of the zodiac signs.
(translated from bilibili)

There are a group of kind and brave green elves living in the tree. They have their own names. ——The long-winded but caring Elf Elders, the brave and strong Alpha, the kind and clever boy, the naughty and clever Mumu, the beautiful and intelligent Ami and the innocent and lovely Nini, they together form the happy green elves family . Every green elf has a healthy, positive, and constantly upward mentality. They also have joy, anger, sorrow, and joy like children. They have to learn, like to play, and are innocent and naughty. The difference is that green elf has wings to fly, superpowers and battle magic.

The cat-eye kid Bao Dada is happier than anyone, because when trouble strikes, there is always wisdom in his mind that blooms like fireworks. Who is Cat Eye Boy Bao Dada? Simply put, he is a bubbling smart boy, his eyes are piercing like a cat, and his hair is messy and stylish like Einstein! Bao Dada’s uncle and well-known robotics scientist, Mr. Bao Cambridge, lived in Bao Dada’s home when he returned from a business trip. He is currently developing a robot named "Cambridge II", preparing to participate in the World Robotics Competition. Uncle Bao came to Bao Dada's school as a special guest to give a lecture. Bao Dada immediately became famous and was spotted by the bragging radio. Unexpectedly, his boasting caused a series of troubles to his uncle, and was used by his classmate and robot magician Tang Oxford. Is Tang Oxford a friend or an enemy of his uncle? In the carnival scene of the Robot Contest, can Uncle Bao Cambridge and his Cambridge No. 2 robot win the championship as they wish? At the critical moment, Bao Dada stepped forward to start an uncle defense battle!

Before leaving, a magical stone flew close to Qiqi's pocket. At night, the stone suddenly glowed, and a spirit appeared. The elves claim to be noisy, come from Dream Manor, and can summon him through this gem. Qiqi and Lele are longing for Dream Manor, so the elves take them to the beautiful Dream Manor. In order to solve this threat, Panhu went through hardships to the mountains and seas where monsters infested, looking for Pangu's axe to open the sky. In the mountains and seas, Panhu and Xin Nu met. Later, the Huaxia tribe was attacked by the dog Rong tribe controlled by the wolf demon. Panhu stepped forward to help the Huaxia tribe repel the dog Rong attack. Emperor Gao Xin agreed to Panhu's request and betrothed Xin Nu to Panhu, and the two tribes married. After Panhu and Xin Nu had lived happily for many years, the wolf demon who recovered her skills sought revenge. Panhu died with the wolf demon to protect the safety of the tribe, while Xin Nu turned into a "Xin Nuyan" and waited for Panhu's return.

In order to return to the heavenly realm, they must help bring happiness to humans and rebuild their virtue. The outcast gods reluctantly grant human wishes and accumulate points in their "god phones" to be able to return to heaven. They aim to perform good deeds on particularly auspicious days to maximize point accumulation. Despite their best efforts at accumulating virtue, sometimes the Seven Gods of Fortune end up bringing misfortune to humans. When they fail, they lose points, further prolonging their stay on Awaji Island.

synopsis:
In 1911, the ancient city of Wuchang was stationed with an army based on Western military ideas, called the New Army. Like other new-style troops across the country, they pinned the Qing Dynasty’s last hope to maintain its shaky rule.

This group of people are collectively called the Revolutionary Party, and they belong to three different organizations-the Japanese Association, the Gongjin Society, and the Literary Society. With the cover of church activities and literary activities, they secretly planned a violent revolution. In order to succeed, the Revolutionary Party came up with the genius idea of ​​recruiting soldiers from the new army to join the revolution. They gradually gathered uprising forces within the army, while waiting for the opportunity of the revolution...
　　 In May, a mass movement took place in the neighboring province of Sichuan. The tense ruler hurriedly dispatched some new troops from Wuchang to suppress it. The military strength in Wuchang city declined, and the Revolutionary Party felt that the time for an uprising had arrived. However, the process of the uprising was full of twists and turns: When the leader of the Revolutionary Party deployed the uprising arrangement, the soldiers of the Nanhu Pao Camp in Chengnan accidentally leaked news of the uprising due to drinking and making trouble. The revolution failed for the first time; the Revolutionary Party manufactured explosives in the Hankou Concession. At the time, the operation error caused the bomb to explode, the list of revolutionary party members was searched, the leader of the revolutionary party was forced to flee the city, and the revolutionary plan failed for the second time; the revolutionary party decided to advance the uprising, but the ruler blocked the whole city and the news of the uprising was not available It was communicated to the soldiers in time, and the uprising plan failed for the third time; during this period, the ruler launched a hysterical counterattack, conducted a large-scale search of the city, and killed the backbone of the Revolutionary Party...
　　 In the most critical time, the soldiers at the bottom were determined to save themselves. In the evening of October 10th, the uprising broke out with a gunshot from the soldiers of the uprising. Soldiers from all military camps heard the gunshots and all took part in the action. They aimed their artillery at the Governor's Mansion. After fierce fighting, the Qing army retreated steadily and high-ranking officials fled. In the early morning of the 11th, the entire Wuchang city was completely controlled by the Revolutionary Party. At dawn, the 18-star flag of the Revolutionary Party was planted on the tower of Wuchang.
　　 On October 17, 1911, a ceremony to symbolize victory and a call for revolution to the whole country was held in Wuchang Yuemachang. People were very excited. This uprising and the ensuing national revolution put an end to China's monarchy for more than two thousand years.
